The paper proposes an auction-based model for pricing and data allocation in big data services, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the impact of data size on the performance of big data analytics, which relates to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of machine learning algorithms in big data analytics also suggests the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
